  "note": "Replace {alias} with your IdP alias. Register the callback_url in your upstream IdP application settings."

}



SECTION 5

Keycloak Admin API Operations





When the control plane receives an identity provider registration request, the following Keycloak Admin API calls are made. The control plane translates between Foundry IAM's simplified config model and Keycloak's full identity provider representation.



5.1 OIDC IdP Registration Sequence

Step

Keycloak Admin API Call

Notes

1

POST /admin/realms/{realm}/identity-provider/instances

Create IdP with providerId=oidc and all config attributes

2

POST /admin/realms/{realm}/identity-provider/instances/{alias}/mappers (per mapper)

Create attribute mappers from attribute_mappers array

3

GET /admin/realms/{realm}/identity-provider/instances/{alias}

Verify creation and retrieve internal ID

4

Encrypt and store

Encrypt full config with AES-256-GCM and store in identity_providers table



5.2 SAML IdP Registration Sequence

Step

Keycloak Admin API Call

Notes

1

POST /admin/realms/{realm}/identity-provider/instances

Create IdP with providerId=saml

2

Set SAML-specific attributes

signingCertificate, singleSignOnServiceUrl, validateSignature, nameIDPolicyFormat, wantAssertionsSigned

3

Create mappers

SAML attribute mappers translate XML attribute names to KC user attributes

4

GET .../descriptor

Retrieve SP metadata for display in portal (for customer to give to their IdP)



5.3 Keycloak Identity Provider Config Object (OIDC)

