SECTION 8

Email Domain Routing (Home Realm Discovery)





Home Realm Discovery allows Foundry IAM to automatically redirect a user to the correct IdP based on their email address domain, without the user having to manually select their provider. This is essential for enterprise SSO UX.



8.1 How It Works

User enters email: jane@acme.com on the Keycloak login page

  ↓

Keycloak checks if any IdP has 'acme.com' in domain_hints

  ↓ (match found: acme-okta IdP)

User is automatically redirected to Okta without seeing the Foundry IAM password field

  ↓

User authenticates with Okta → returns to Keycloak → JWT issued



No match: user sees Foundry IAM login form (password or social buttons)



8.2 Configuration

Domain hints are stored in the identity_providers.domain_hints array and must be synced to Keycloak's Identity Provider hintedDomain attribute. This is set during IdP creation and updated via PATCH.



8.3 Conflict Detection

Validation Rule

Two IdPs in the same workspace cannot claim the same email domain. The control plane must validate uniqueness of domain hints within a workspace before registering. Return 409 with error code domain_already_claimed if a conflict is detected.



SECTION 9

Test Matrix





Test ID

Scenario

Expected Result

FED-001

Register OIDC IdP (Okta) with valid config

201, IdP visible in Keycloak Admin, callback URL returned

FED-002

Register SAML IdP (Azure AD) with valid config

201, IdP visible in Keycloak Admin with SAML attributes

FED-003

Register Google social IdP

201, Google sign-in button appears on realm login page

FED-004

OIDC login flow end-to-end (test Okta)

User redirected to Okta, authenticates, returns with Foundry IAM JWT

FED-005

SAML login flow end-to-end (test Azure AD)

User redirected to Azure AD, SAML assertion processed, JWT issued

FED-006

Email domain routing — acme.com auto-routes to Okta

User entering acme.com email redirected to Okta without password field

FED-007

Duplicate domain hint in same workspace

409 with error code domain_already_claimed

FED-008

Attribute mapping — email synced from upstream

Federated user's Keycloak email matches upstream IdP email claim

FED-009

Attribute mapping — role mapper assigns tenant_admin based on group claim

User with 'foundry-admins' group in Okta gets tenant_admin role in Keycloak

FED-010

Disable IdP — login button removed

IdP button no longer appears on realm login page. Existing federated sessions unaffected until expiry.

FED-011

Delete IdP — federated users retain record but cannot SSO

IdP removed from Keycloak. scim_users or KC users with link still exist but link is broken.

FED-012

Update client secret — new secret applied to Keycloak

Subsequent OIDC flows use new secret. Old secret no longer valid with upstream.

FED-013

SAML SP metadata URL returns valid XML

GET .../descriptor returns parseable SAML metadata with correct entityID

FED-014

Tenant isolation — IdP in workspace A not visible from workspace B

IdP list for workspace B is empty / does not include A's IdP

FED-015

Test URL for OIDC IdP initiates auth flow

Browser redirect to upstream IdP login

FED-016

Register IdP with duplicate alias in same workspace

409 with error code alias_already_exists



9.1 Recommended Test Tooling

Tool

Purpose

Okta Developer Account

Free. Create OIDC app, point redirect URI to local Keycloak via ngrok. Full real OIDC test.

Azure AD Free Tenant

Free Microsoft account. Create Enterprise App with SAML for real SAML brokering test.

Google Cloud Console

Free tier. Create OAuth2 credentials for Google social IdP test.

Mock OIDC server (node-oidc-provider)

Docker-based mock OIDC server for offline testing without external accounts.

ngrok

Required to expose local Keycloak realm to external IdPs for callback during testing.

Keycloak Identity Broker UI

Admin Console → Identity Providers. Use to verify configurations are correctly applied after control plane API calls.



